Woolly Mammoth: Secrets from the Ice (BBC 1080p)

Science Documentary hosted by Alice Roberts, published by BBC in 2012 - English narration. 
http://docuwiki.net/images/d/d6/Woolly-Mammoth-Secrets-from-the-Ice-BBC-1080p-Cover.jpg

Information
------------------------------
Professor Alice Roberts reveals the natural history of the most famous of ice age animals - the woolly mammoth. Mammoths have transfixed humans since the depths of the last ice age, when their herds roamed across what is now Europe and Asia. Although these curious members of the elephant family have now been extinct for thousands of years, scientists can now paint an incredibly detailed picture of their lives thanks to whole carcasses that have been beautifully preserved in the Siberian permafrost.
Alice meets the scientists who are using the latest genetic, chemical and molecular tests to reveal the adaptations that allowed mammoths to evolve from their origins in the tropics to surviving the extremes of Siberia. And in a dramatic end to the film, she helps unveil a brand new woolly mammoth carcass that may shed new light on our own ancestors' role in their extinction.
